---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Callout from '../../components/Callout.astro';

export const title = "Cannabis Extraction Licensing";
---

<Layout 
  title="Cannabis Extraction Licensing | Maine Dispensary Guide" 
  description="Complete guide to cannabis extraction licensing in Maine. Regulations, requirements, and best practices for hash oil and concentrate production."
  heroImage="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1581091226825-a6a2a5aee158?auto=format&fit=crop&q=80&w=1200&h=400"
>
  <article>
    <div class="article-header">
      <h1>Cannabis Extraction Licensing</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Navigating Maine's extraction licensing requirements</p>
    </div>

    <section>
      <h2>Overview</h2>
      <p>Cannabis extraction—the process of producing concentrates, hash oils, and other concentrated products—is a specialized area of the cannabis industry requiring additional licensing and compliance in Maine. Whether you're interested in producing BHO, rosin, CO2 extracts, or other concentrates, understanding the regulatory landscape is essential for success. Before moving forward, familiarize yourself with the <a href="/guides/maine-dispensary-license/">licensing process</a> essential for success.</p>
    </section>

    <Callout title="Excellence in Compliance" type="success">
      Mastering this aspect of your business is a badge of professional excellence. It ensures longevity and demonstrates your commitment to the highest standards of the Maine cannabis industry.
    </Callout>


    <section>
      <h2>License Types</h2>
      <p>Maine requires specific licensing for extraction operations. Under <a href="https://www.maine.gov/dafs/ocp/rules" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Maine OCP regulations</a>, you may need:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Manufacturing License</strong> - For commercial extraction operations</li>
        <li><strong>Processing License</strong> - For converting raw material to concentrates</li>
        <li><strong>Products Manufacturing</strong> - For creating infused products</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Extraction Methods</h2>
      <p>Different methods have different regulatory requirements:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Solvent-based (BHO, PHO)</strong> - Requires specialized equipment, explosive-proof facilities</li>
        <li><strong>CO2 Extraction</strong> - Pressurized equipment, FDA-approved method</li>
        <li><strong>Rosin/Heat Press</strong> - Solventless, lower regulatory burden</li>
        <li><strong>Ice Water Hash</strong> - Solventless, simplest to start</li>
        <li><strong>Ethanol Extraction</strong> - Common, requires proper handling</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Facility Requirements</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Explosion-proof electrical and ventilation systems</li>
        <li>Proper solvent storage and handling</li>
        <li>Closed-loop systems for hydrocarbon extractions</li>
        <li>Professional-grade extraction equipment</li>
        <li>Compliance with fire and building codes</li>
        <li>Security systems and access controls</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Compliance Requirements</h2>
      <p>Under <a href="https://www.maine.gov/dafs/ocp/adult-use/rules" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Maine adult-use rules</a>:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Detailed standard operating procedures (SOPs)</li>
        <li>Employee training on safety and compliance</li>
        <li>Proper waste disposal for solvents and materials</li>
        <li>Testing of all products for residual solvents</li>
        <li>Seed-to-sale tracking integration</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Investment Overview</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Category</th><th>Estimated Cost</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Equipment</td><td>$50,000-500,000+</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Facility Build-out</td><td>$100,000-300,000</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Licensing</td><td>$5,000-15,000</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Total <a href="/guides/maine-dispensary-costs/">Investment</a></td><td>$150,000-800,000+</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section class="further-reading">
      <h2>Further Reading</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://www.maine.gov/dafs/ocp/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Maine Office of Cannabis Policy (OCP)</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.maine.gov/dafs/ocp/rules" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Maine Cannabis Rules</a></li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="disclaimer">
      <p><em>This is for informational purposes only and does not constitute legal or financial advice. Consult with qualified professionals.</em></p>
    </section>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  article { max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .article-header { margin-bottom: 2rem; padding-bottom: 1.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  .subtitle { font-size: 1.25rem; color: var(--color-text-light); }
  section { margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  section h2, section h3 { margin-top: 1.5rem; }
  section h2:first-child { margin-top: 0; }
  table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 1rem 0; }
  th, td { padding: 0.75rem; text-align: left; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  th { background: var(--color-background); }
  ul { padding-left: 1.5rem; }
  li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .disclaimer { background: #fff3cd; border: 1px solid #ffc107; padding: 1rem; border-radius: 0.5rem; font-size: 0.875rem; margin-top: 2rem; }
  .further-reading { background: rgba(88, 129, 87, 0.05); padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 1rem; margin-top: 3rem; }
  .further-reading h2 { margin-top: 0; font-size: 1.25rem; }
</style>
